// Release GUI builds are windowless: no console flashes behind the browser
// window on launch. DEBUG builds keep the console attached so `diag_log` /
// eprintln diagnostics and the `--type screenshot/run-js/probe/render` CLI
// output remain visible during development and `cargo test` (tests always
// build in debug, so this attr never affects them). Release CLI modes still
// write to stdout/stderr when launched from an existing console (Windows
// inherits the parent console); they only lack an auto-allocated console when
// double-clicked, which is correct for a GUI app.
#![cfg_attr(not(debug_assertions), windows_subsystem = "windows")]

//! `conclave` — entry point for every process role.
//!
//! Dispatches on `--type`:
//! - (no flag) → browser process (UI). Not implemented yet.
//! - `--type fetch <url>` → M0 CLI fetcher demo. Pulls a URL over HTTP/1.1
//!   and prints the response to stdout.
//! - Future: `--type renderer`, `--type network`, `--type gpu`,
//!   `--type extension` once the multi-process split lands in M4.

